$ V14: RBAR zero-offset coupling
$ 1 CBAR element, L=1.0 m, fixed at GID 1, CBAR tip at GID 2
$ GID 3 is coincident with GID 2; RBAR connects GA=2 (independent) to GB=3 (dependent)
$ Force 1000 N in +Y applied at GID 3 (the dependent grid)
$ With d=(0,0,0), R=identity so u[GID3] = u[GID2] exactly
$ Expected: Ty[GID2] = PL^3/3EI (same as bare cantilever and V13)
$
SOL 101
$
SUBCASE 1
  TITLE = RBAR Zero-Offset Coupling
  SPC = 1
  LOAD = 10
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
$
BEGIN BULK
$
GRID, 1, , 0.0, 0.0, 0.0
GRID, 2, , 1.0, 0.0, 0.0
GRID, 3, , 1.0, 0.0, 0.0
$
MAT1, 1, 2.0e11, 7.692e10, 0.3, 7850.0
$
PBAR, 1, 1, 0.05, 8.333e-4, 8.333e-4, 1.406e-3
$
CBAR, 1, 1, 1, 2, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
$
RBAR, 1, 2, 3
$
SPC1, 1, 123456, 1
$
FORCE, 10, 3, 0, 1000.0, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
$
ENDDATA
